cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with speech recognition, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and hence, is likely to be categorized under cs.CL.
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with speech recognition, which involves sound processing, and hence, can be categorized under cs.SD.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a simplified end-to-end training method for speech recognition using gradient descent, which is a machine learning technique. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.LG.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.AI.
5. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with speech recognition, which involves signal processing techniques. Hence, it can be categorized under cs.SI.
